<h3>The components</h3>

<p>Each component inlcudes a demo page with an example. Run them locally using a server (I recommend <a href="https://www.11ty.dev/docs/dev-server/" target="_blank">Eleventy Dev Server</a>). Curernt components:</p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="https://codeberg.org/patrickgrey/naked-web-components/src/branch/main/naked-sticky-overflow" target="_blank"><span style="display:inline-block;margin-inline:0.25em;">{% include '../../_shared/images/icons/codeberg-logo_icon_blue.svg' %}</span>naked-sticky-overflow</a>
    <p>I'm very proud of the name of this one! Adding scrolling to an element can save your layout but elements with <code>position: sticky</code> will fail. This component lets sticky work with a scrolling solution. It will <strong>progressively enhance</strong> an existing overflow.</p></li>
    
    <li><a href="https://codeberg.org/patrickgrey/naked-web-components/src/branch/main/naked-table-sort" target="_blank"><span style="display:inline-block;margin-inline:0.25em;">{% include '../../_shared/images/icons/codeberg-logo_icon_blue.svg' %}</span>naked-table-sort</a>
    <p>Tables. Sorted!</p></li>

    <li><a href="https://codeberg.org/patrickgrey/naked-web-components/src/branch/main/naked-table-stripe-sort" target="_blank"><span style="display:inline-block;margin-inline:0.25em;">{% include '../../_shared/images/icons/codeberg-logo_icon_blue.svg' %}</span>naked-table-stripe-sort</a>
    <p>If a table has alternating table row colours, when it is filtered or sorted, the alternation can get messed up. As far
            as I know,
            we cannot fix this with CSS (yet) so this component listens for changes in the tbody trs and reapplies user
            specified
            classes to each visible row.</p></li>

    <li><a href="https://codeberg.org/patrickgrey/naked-web-components/src/branch/main/naked-filter" target="_blank"><span style="display:inline-block;margin-inline:0.25em;">{% include '../../_shared/images/icons/codeberg-logo_icon_blue.svg' %}</span>naked-filter</a>
    <p>Filter things within a container. Could be a table, could be something else - oooh the mystery oooohh!</p></li>

    <li><a href="https://codeberg.org/patrickgrey/naked-web-components/src/branch/main/naked-x-of-x" target="_blank"><span style="display:inline-block;margin-inline:0.25em;">{% include '../../_shared/images/icons/codeberg-logo_icon_blue.svg' %}</span>naked-x-of-x</a>
    <p>Nothing to do with the hellsite! Count the number of visible things from a total of things. Catchy language, I know.</p></li>

</ul>
